remarks: If as a conseqence of the occurence of the circumstance ` ph ` , when the obstacle ` ps ` is removed, ` ch ` takes place, then from the circumstance that ` ch ` does not take place while ` ph ` occurs the occurence of the obstacle ` ps ` can be inferred.  Closed form of ~ con1d .  Proposition 34 of [Frege1879] p. 45.  (Contributed by RP, 24-Dec-2019.) (Proof modification is discouraged.)
